        <li><div>Switch your fleet to electric or hybrid:  </div><br>This apply if your company uses business cars or trucks, and especially if the fleet is getting old (therefore more polluting). This is an investment but it will allow you to redeem taxes cost and maybe benefit from governmental or car dealer discounts.</li><br>
        <li><div>Optimize your employees transportation:  </div><br>Encourage your employees to have video conference meetings (Skype, FaceTime, Zoom) instead of flying, support telecommuting by setting up a dedicated IT rules of procedure. Finally, public transportation could be promoted by paying off 50% off their montly transport pass, as it is compulsory in some countries. </li><br>
        <li><div>Reorganize the office furnitures:  </div><br>This includes displaying different waste containers to encourage employees to do selective sorting to recycle their waste, sensibilise employees regarding electricity consumptions and install energy efficient lighting.</li><br>
        <li><div>Reduce heading and AC consumption: </div><br>Try (if possible) reviewing the insulation of the premises, installing double glazing and installing optimal timing control.</li>
